description:
Responsibilities: 


Assist in project implementation, testing & commissioning, quality assurance and documentation; 
Provide first line maintenance service to network and LED display panels;
Assist in installation and configuration of network and computer systems;
Manage contractors’ work progress to fulfill the project requirement; and
Handle ad hoc tasks as assigned.
Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above in Electronic Engineering or IT-related disciplines;
At least 3 years' relevant experiences in IT and or ELV equipment installation, maintenance and trouble shooting;

Knowledge in network switches, PC/Server setup and configuration;
Hands-on knowledge of AutoCAD is highly preferable;
Self-motivated and able to work independently under tight deadline with minimum supervision;
Good command of spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin.

Please send your full detailed resume with expected salary and date available to The Human Resources Manager, NEC Hong Kong Limited, 25th Floor, The Metropolis Tower, 10 Metropolis Drive, Hunghom, Kowloon or by e-mail.

Personal data provided by job applicant will be used strictly in accordance with employer's personal data policy, a copy of which will be provided immediately upon request.

Responsibilities:

Attend to helpdesk phone calls and call registration into helpdesk system;
Create and maintain Helpdesk analysis report and records;
Perform daily system operations – include batch job submission, data backup, etc.;
Provide technical support services to internal users and external customers;
Administer / monitor system (data centre facilities, networks, IT systems, etc.);
Assist Data Centre Supervisor and System/Network Engineer with problem diagnosis;
Co-ordinate with internal team / vendor to follow up and fix problem, including internal / external incident and problem escalation

Requirements:     

1 year working experience in computer and data network operations
Experience in hotline / data centre operations and support; in telecommunication industry, Data Centre or Helpdesk are definite advantage
Candidates are required to work in shift, good phone manner and attitude is essential

We offer competitive salary package and career development opportunity.  Interested parties, please apply with full resume, present and expected salary, by clicking “APPLY NOW”.  Please quote the reference number on the e-mail subject.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for consideration of your application for the relevant post within HGC Global Communications Limited. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly according to our Personal Information Collection Statement, a copy of which will be available upon written request. Information of unsuccessful candidates will be destroyed within six months.

Job Description:

Support service through hot line and email;
Gather preliminary information and pass to second line support;
Understand customer requirement, provide solution through usage of ITIS software package;
Write up of customer requirement;
Conduct system testing;
Provide user training;
Prepare and maintain user documentation, such as user manual, training manual, etc.

Job Requirement:

With 2 year or above relevant experience;
Diploma or equivalent is a plus;
Knowledge in logistics, freight forwarding, and transportation is a plus;
Experience in using ERP systems of any kind is a plus;
Responsive, good communication/interpersonal skills, and open to new tasks/ exposure;
Able to listen to customers and understand their key concerns in order to achieve better services and solutions (with analytical mindset);
Patient, helpful, eager to help customer resolving issues relating to services offered;
Good command of spoken & written English and/or Chinese.

Employees with good performance will be promoted.



We are equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates.

Job Responsibilities:
Serve as the first-line support to staff members, students and parents of the Academy;
Provide support to software, network, e-mail, office applications and educational software issues;
Responsible for the opening, assignment, monitoring and closing of IT service tickets via the ticketing system;
Perform administrative duties such as maintaining hardware and software inventory, setting up of event schedule calendar and keeping track of loaned equipment and laptops etc.; and
Assist IT related daily activities.
Requirements:
Relevant education background in either Information System, Information Technology or Computer Science disciplines;
Good understanding on the use of computer systems, mobile devices and other technical products;
Excellent telephone manner and communication skills;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Cantonese (including Mandarin);
Ability to diagnose and resolve basic technical issues;
Ability to work independently; and
Be a good team player.
The ISF Foundation, Academy & Pre-School are committed to ensuring safety and well-being of our students. We hold high standards of recruitment practices with specific attention to child protection. All applicants must be willing to undergo relevant background checks and screenings.
Free Shuttle Bus travelling to and from The ISF Academy will be provided:
Route: North Point > Admiralty Centre > Causeway Bay > Aberdeen > The ISF Academy
Application Deadline: 28 January 2022

Remuneration will commensurate with qualifications and experience. We will offer an attractive benefits package including medical, life insurance, and opportunities for professional development and continuing education to the right candidate. Please submit your application by completing the Application Form, Reference Check Statement which could be downloaded from our website: www.isf.edu.hk together with full Curriculum Vitae and Covering Letter.Please quote with our “Ref: no.” by email via "Apply Now"


Personal data is collected for employment purposes only.

Job Responsibilities: 

Provide 1st-level application support to system users over WhatsApp, email and phone;
Dispatch support ticket to 2nd-level support when necessary;
Perform application testing;
Document support workflow and create operation manuals;
Monitor the performance and operation of production systems, response to system alert and incident; and
 Work closely with development teams, business analysts to enhance existing systems.

Requirements: 

Diploma or above in any discipline;
Major in Information Technology or Computer related disciplines is an advantage;
1 year of experience in helpdesk related work in supporting business applications;
Strong business application workflow mindset;
Experience in writing technical document or IT Policy is an advantage;
Good command in Cantonese and English, Putonghua is an advantage;
Willing to learn, self-initiative and work independently; and
Good interpersonal skill, telephone manner and service attitude.
